The team of Czech and German scientists is testing new connections to prevent the spread of HIV viruses in the organism.
The main advantage of the improved substance is that it also acts in the viruses that are already resistant to drugs.
This fact outweighs the disadvantage that the connection to common virus variants does not work as much as one of the existing medicines.
The AIDS disease cannot be cured yet.
However, patients can extend their life and prevent the proliferation of HIV viruses in the body.
However, your administration is accompanied by a whole range of side effects.
Incomplete suppression of virus reproduction also results in the development of resistance viruses that are no longer effective.
The work of experts from three institutes of the Academy of Sciences CR, the VSCHT (Chemical Technology University) Prague and the University of Heidelberg opens the way to dealing with virus resistance.
They have shown that the substances called metalocarborans act on the protein responsible for the proliferation of the HIV virus.
Metalocarborans are compounds of boron, hydrogen, carbon and cobalt.
