New vehicle assessment programmes
In these days of weather and accidents, not only the KFZ workshops deserve
Every day, thousands of vehicles involved in an accident are dragged into the workshops where a verifier has to assess the damage caused and the costs of repair.
No accident is the same and the calculation of the costs of the parts and working hours can be a long and complicated task.
The calculation of the repair costs of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros per hand, including the parts and working hours, can take up to two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the support of the latest computer tools, it is a matter of minutes.
That is why almost 100% of the evaluators use this kind of system.
The service and application providers for the assessment of accidents and repairs collect the information they receive from the manufacturers in order to process them and offer them to their customers in the form of a useful programme.
In Spain, Audtex, part of the American group Solera, is the market leader; 80% of all opinions are produced with their products.
The other two companies competing with the tool market for review and preparation of a report are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data that the manufacturers provide is anything but easy.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, the sales manager of Audtex, 63 manufacturers and importers are working together, each of them providing the information in a different format.
Moreover, the amount of data to be processed is becoming more and more, up to the point that more versions, variants and motorists have been on the market in the last five years than in the whole fifteen years before.
As soon as a new car comes on the market, the work starts for the companies.
It is a difficult task, because every single one of the Aberthousand parts of the vehicle must be catagolised and its price entered.
In addition, a "intelligent" graphic image is created by each model, on which you can "click on" different parts of the vehicle.
If this is a much-sold model, work can be completed in a week if the procedure is in progress.
If this is a less common car, it can take up to three or four months. At present, Audtex has complete information for 99.2% of the cars sold in Spain.
Among the more exclusive models, for example, they have information about the Porsche models, but not about Ferrari or Lamborghini.
With regard to the road vehicle park, it is more than 99%.
In order to carry out the documentation work and the production of databases, Audtex has eight centres distributed worldwide (Spain, France, Germany, the USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in certain brands.
The national headquarters are in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanics experts) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audtex is investing 90 million euros a year in the development of these databases.
Every month they record 2.5 million data and their customers get the updates every second day.
The development of this enormous flow of information allows companies to use it in different ways and thus offer different products.
The most common use is the use for repairs and repairs, but there are also tools, depending on the country, for the management of scrap parts or for the calculation of the total or residual value of a car.
The only company that is informed about a guide about the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audtex does not offer this offer in Spain, but in the United States.
When looking at the products that Audtex offers, it is easy to get an overview of the type of support it gives to industry experts.
This company offers ten different tools, with the star of the products AudaPlus, a standard solution to test accidents for the evaluators.
It includes vehicles, motorcycles and light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it contains the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the paint prices.
This tool is paid according to the purpose of use, i.e. for each opinion.
It will be the most expensive for customers who rarely use it, up to ten times a month, namely 5.75 euros a month.
On the other hand, any insurance company that produces thousands of opinions is negotiating the price with Audtex.
With other products, such as Audavin, you can fully identify a vehicle and the equipment with which it was running from the assembly board only by means of the chassis number.
AudaGlass deals with the vehicle discs, and AudaSubastas is an open service on the Internet for the specialist market, with which you can offer for vehicles that have been declared to be total damage.
Your statistical service is very useful in identifying trends, conducting geodemographic analyses or in obtaining information on the differences by brand and model.
For example, it is possible to examine how many models of a particular car brand had to go to the workshop due to the breaks or how many of them were involved in a serious accident during a certain period of time.
