estimate of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audtex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in only four steps: identification of the vehicle, search of the spare part, creation and production of a cost estimate.
The easy handling of these systems is a basic condition, especially to convince the older professionals who are usually more or less against the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger vehicles, 109 road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 small vehicles and 44 trucks.
Of course you need a computer with internet connection for use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified using the chassis number, a graphic of the model appears and then the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price for working hours, prices or discounts and then have the estimate printed out and passed on to his customers.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for review such as AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of use for this tool is 350 euros a year, an amount that the customer can easily pay.
